 in radius. Multiple transitions of CH3CN, HNCO and\nCH3OH provide the rotation temperatures, suggesting that the central source of\nMCN-a has an intrinsic bolometric luminosity of ~10^6 Lsun. These results have\nrevealed the structure and kinematics of MCN-a at its intermediate radii. With\nno broad-line H30alpha emission detected, MCN-a may be in the earliest phase of\nmassive star formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 10 Apr 2022 07:01:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 20 May 2022 20:00:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-08"}
